fields.short_desc: A chance to see the players of tomorrow as easylaughs graduates and players from around Amsterdam form teams and compete for the audience approval. If you are an easylaughs graduate and want to get some more stage time then contact us at info@easylaughs.nl

fields.short_desc:
Do you have a noisy neighbour? An irritating co-worker, a nagging partner? Bring your grievances to easylaughs and seek justice!

Audience complaints are given a fair trial in this improvised courtroom battle, and once all the evidence has been heard, the audience decides the final verdict: innocent or guilty!
fields.title: Courtroom Drama

fields.short_desc: Its the last Friday of the term and the easylaughs cast are celebrating a family Christmas together. Some games, some songs, some Christmas crackers, maybe even a mince pie or two... its the only place to be this Christmas so pull up a seat by the fire and get festive!
fields.title: easylaughs Family Christmas

fields.short_desc:

So come along and show them some improv love!

fields.short_desc: Peter likes a challenge. This one is to create a movie on the spot in a random genre chosen by a panel of top Hollywood producers (yes, that's you). This plus re-imagining some classic scenes should keep him occupied and give those tricky producers what they want.

fields.late_extra_inf: Its Chinese vs Japanese in the honorable battle of Fah Cue.

“Inside Llewyn Davis,” Joel and Ethan Coen’s darkly comic odyssey set against the 1960s New York folk-music scene, swept the National Society of Film Critics’ top prizes on Saturday, winning awards for picture, director, actor Oscar Isaac and cinematography.

The Coens’ film has gone largely unrecognized by critics’ groups this season, apart from a picture prize from the Toronto Film Critics Assn. The New York Film Critics Circle gave its top award to “American Hustle,” while the Los Angeles Film Critics’ Assn. split its honors between “Gravity” and “Her.”
fields.early_extra_inf:
a·loneness n.
Synonyms: alone, lonely, lonesome, solitary

These adjectives describe lack of companionship. Alone emphasizes being apart from others but does not necessarily imply unhappiness: "I am never less alone, than when I am alone" (James Howell).

fields.desc: Chondrichthyes (/kɒnˈdrɪkθɨ.iːz/; from Greek χονδρ- chondr- 'cartilage', ἰχθύς ichthys 'fish') or cartilaginous fishes are jawed fish with paired fins, paired nares, scales, a heart with its chambers in series, and skeletons made of cartilage rather than bone. The class is divided into two subclasses: Elasmobranchii (sharks, rays and skates) and Holocephali (chimaeras, sometimes called ghost sharks, which are sometimes separated into their own class).
